Sentencas: The stability of micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell (MT-SOFC) is predicted at ambient and operating temperatures via simulation method.
Titulo: Analysis of micro-tubular SOFC stability under ambient and operating temperatures

Sentencas: The results reveal that as long as the anode failure probability satisfies the failure criterion of 1E-6 at ambient temperature, the anode will retain its structural integrity at operating temperature.
Titulo: Analysis of micro-tubular SOFC stability under ambient and operating temperatures

Sentencas: For the electrolyte or cathode, the stress strength ratio at operating temperature is significantly higher than that at ambient temperature.
Titulo: Analysis of micro-tubular SOFC stability under ambient and operating temperatures

Sentencas: For an inappropriate component thickness, the cathode maybe fractures at operating temperature.
Titulo: Analysis of micro-tubular SOFC stability under ambient and operating temperatures

Sentencas: In order to ensure the stability of MT-SOFC, the cathode thickness must be smaller than the maximum cathode thickness to (t(max-cathode)), which is derived from: t(max-cathode) = 5.49 + 5.54t(e) (C) 2018 Published by Elsevier Ltd on behalf of The editorial office of Journal of Materials Science & Technology.
